<subSubSection pageId="95" pageNumber="96" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="95.[151,1437,1209,1633]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1534,1560]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nobili" authorityYear="1901" box="[322,589,1534,1560]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="95" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="holotrichus">
<emphasis box="[322,589,1534,1560]" italics="true" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">Petrolisthes holotrichus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to be uncommon in 
<collectingCountry box="[911,1000,1534,1560]" name="Panama" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">Panama</collectingCountry>
and was known, prior to Haig’s (1957, 1960) records, only from the 
<typeStatus box="[473,521,1570,1596]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">type</typeStatus>
material of 
<bibRefCitation author="Nobili, G." box="[654,809,1570,1596]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref75569" refString="Nobili, G. (1901) Decapodi raccolti dal Dr. Filippo Silvestri nell' America Meridionale. Bollettino dei Musei di Zoologia e di Anatomia Comparata della R. Universita di Torino, 16 (402), 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1901">Nobili (1901)</bibRefCitation>
. The species is easily recognisable by its squarish format and “fuzzy” appearance, due to the densely pilose carapace and P1–4 (
<figureCitation box="[942,1026,1606,1633]" captionStart="FIGURE 58" captionStartId="96.[151,250,1945,1969]" captionTargetBox="[274,1312,452,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-123@96.[274,1312,452,1922]" captionTargetPageId="96" captionText="FIGURE 58. Petrolisthes holotrichus Nobili, 1901: A, B, ovigerous female (cl 5.3 mm, cw 5.5 mm) from Las Perlas Islands, Panama (MZUSP 33958), dorsal (A) and ventral (B) views [photographs by AA]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5532351" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5532351/files/figure.png" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
